Field Detail

HINT_CALLBACK_NOT_INITIALIZED

public static final int HINT_CALLBACK_NOT_INITIALIZED
Hint that a callback is used prior to initialization. Note that an exception with this hint may be thrown by the system itself and not necessarily by the implementation of the callback.

Method Detail

getHint

public int getHint()
Returns an integer which can give the measurement or job a hint of the cause of the exception. The values 0-99 are reserved for general purpose hints. The meaning of a value above 100 is specific for the callback and should be well documented.

Returns:
Interpretable hint for the reason of the exception. Returns -1 if no hint is available.
